    "content": "Never Let You Go - Third Eye Blind - Blue \r\nTABBED BY scott_schaffer@hotmail.com\r\nrevised by Scott Schaffer, too\r\n \r\n[tab]INTRO (Guitar intro then this slide)\r\nG|------14-- \r\nD|--/14----- \r\nA|---------- \r\nE|----------[/tab]\r\n \r\n[tab]VERSES \r\nG|------------------------- \r\nD|--2----------2----------- \r\nA|----2--0-0-----2--0-0-0-- \r\nE|------------------------- [/tab]\r\n \r\n[tab]BRIDGE (1:50)           (1:50)\r\nG|-------------------6x----9-8-9--------------\r\nD|--2p1h2----------2-6x----------9-7------9---\r\nA|---------2-0-2h4---6x-OR-----------7h10-----\r\nE|-------------------6x----------------------- [/tab]\r\n \r\nINTRO (Guitar E B A)\r\n \r\nVERSE 1 (0:11)\r\n \r\nPRE-CHORUS (0:28)\r\n \r\nCHORUS (0:42)\r\n \r\nVERSE 2 (1:03)\r\n \r\nPRE-CHORUS (1:19)\r\n \r\nCHORUS (1:33)\r\n \r\nBRIDGE (1:50)\r\n \r\nVERSE 3 (2:15) (Guitars Only)\r\n \r\n[tab]PRE-CHORUS (2:30) (Towards the end of the PRE-CHORUS,\r\nG|----------- slide to this E and rapidly play it)\r\nD|--14-14-14- \r\nA|----------- \r\nE|-----------  [/tab]\r\n \r\nCHORUS (2:45)(GUITAR PICKING)\r\n \r\nCHORUS (3:01)\r\n \r\nOUTRO VERSE (3:27)\r\n \r\n[tab]   If that's boring try messing around in Emajor pentatonic.\r\n  G|---------------7-9--|     \r\n  D|-----------7-9------|     \r\n  A|-------7-9----------| or  E F# G# A B C# D# E for you note people\r\n  E|--7-10--------------|[/tab]\r\n \r\n[tab]And for that highly repetitive, but cool, VERSE riff,\r\n Try walking up to the E that the riff starts on.\r\nVERSES \r\nG|-------------------------------|\r\nD|--2----------2--------------2--|\r\nA|----2--0-0-----2--0-0-0h2h4----|\r\nE|-------------------------------|[/tab]",
